    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesnt feel like a transition though. transitions imply something new is coming. with me, it just feels like the lights went out years ago. i'm just going through the motions, doing the chores, talking to people... but there's nobody actually \"home\" anymore. it's like i'm just a walking corpse. a body without a soul. it feels pointless to keep dragging this empty thing around.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
